==English==

===Pronunciation===
*lēch, /liːtʃ/, /<tt>li:tS</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[leach]]
*:[[Rhymes:English:-iːtʃ|Rhymes: -iːtʃ]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[læċe]]''
====Noun==== 
'''leech''' (pl. ''leeches'')

# an aquatic blood-sucking animal (Hirudo)
# a person who extorts profit from others
# (obsolete) a [[physician]]

===Etymology===
Middle English, maybe from Old Norse ''lik''
====Noun==== 
'''leech'''

# (Nautical) The trailing vertical edge of a sail disposed downwind.

